<% content_for :title do %><%= installation_brand_name %> — Customer Support Platform<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>
  <%= installation_brand_name %> is a business customer support application by SamaBrains Solutions. Teams connect Gmail,
  social messaging, and website chat to manage customer conversations in one workspace.
<% end %>

<section class="hero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Customer support application</p>
  <h1><%= installation_brand_name %></h1>
  <p class="lead">
    <strong><%= installation_brand_name %></strong> is a software application that helps businesses and support teams
    manage customer conversations from email, live chat, and social messaging channels in one shared workspace.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>What this application does</h2>
  <p>
    <%= installation_brand_name %> lets organizations connect communication channels—such as
    <strong>Gmail</strong>, <strong>Facebook Messenger</strong>, <strong>Instagram</strong>, and
    <strong>website chat</strong>—so agents can read incoming customer messages, assign conversations,
    collaborate with teammates, and send replies without switching between tools.
  </p>
  <p>
    This application is intended for <strong>businesses and their authorized staff</strong>. It is not a consumer
    social network or personal email client.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>How <%= installation_brand_name %> uses Google user data</h2>
  <p>
    When a workspace administrator chooses to connect a <strong>Gmail inbox</strong>, <%= installation_brand_name %>
    requests permission through Google OAuth to access that mailbox so agents can:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Read incoming customer support emails through the connected Gmail inbox</li>
    <li>Send email replies to customers on behalf of the connected inbox</li>
    <li>Display message content inside the <%= installation_brand_name %> workspace for support workflows</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We use Google user data <strong>only</strong> to provide these inbox features for the account that authorized
    access. We do not use Gmail data for advertising, sell it to third parties, or use it for purposes unrelated to
    customer support. Users can revoke <%= installation_brand_name %>'s access at any time in
    <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Account permissions</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
  Optional <strong>Sign in with Google</strong> uses Google only to authenticate workspace users (email and basic
  profile). It does not grant mailbox access unless the user separately connects a Gmail inbox.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Key features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Unified inbox for customer conversations across channels</li>
    <li>Team assignment, notes, and conversation history</li>
    <li>Gmail inbox connection for inbound and outbound support email</li>
    <li>Social messaging integrations (e.g. Messenger, Instagram) where enabled</li>
    <li>Embeddable website chat widget for your visitors</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Privacy and terms</h2>
  <p>
    We describe how we collect, use, and protect data in our
    <a href="<%= "#{legal_site_url}/privacy" %>">Privacy Policy</a>
    and <a href="<%= "#{legal_site_url}/terms" %>">Terms of Service</a>.
    The privacy policy URL configured for this application matches the link on this page.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Get started</h2>
  <p>
    <a href="/app/login">Sign in</a> to an existing workspace or
    <a href="/app/auth/signup">create a new workspace</a> if registration is enabled on this installation.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>SamaBrains Solutions</strong> (operator of <%= installation_brand_name %>)<br>
    Email: <a href="mailto:info@samabrains.com">info@samabrains.com</a><br>
    Website: <a href="<%= legal_site_url %>"><%= legal_site_url.sub(%r{^https?://}, '') %></a>
  </p>
</section>
